BEMIS BRO. BAG COMPANY, Appellant, v. Charles N. FEIDELSON, Regional Director of the National Labor Relations Board, etc., et al., Appellees. No. 7325. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Jan. 4, 1938. Frank Y. Gladney, of St. Louis, Mo., and S. J. Everett, of Jackson, Tenn., for appellant. Philip G. Phillips, of Cincinnati, Ohio, for appellees.

Before MOORMAN, HICKS, and SIMONS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal in this cause be, and the same is, dismissed, pursuant to agreed motion of counsel.
